\"Honda Certificate of Conformity\">Honda Certificate of Conformity</ref>\n*** Torque : 110&nbsp;lb\u00b7ft (15.2&nbsp;kg/m, 149 Nm) at 4500&nbsp;rpm<ref name=\"Honda Certificate of Conformity\"/>\n*** RPM redline : 6750&nbsp;rpm\n*** Rev-limiter : 7200&nbsp;rpm\n*** Valvetrain : SOHC (4 valves per cylinder)\n*** Fuel Control : OBD-2 MPFI\n\n===D17A9===\n* [[VTEC#VTEC-E|VTEC-E]]\n* Found in:\n** 2001\u20132005 Honda Civic Coupe ES (Europe)\n*** Displacement : {{convert|1668|cc|CID|abbr=on}}\n*** Bore and Stroke : {{convert|75|x|94.4|mm|in|abbr=on}}\n*** Rod Length : 140&nbsp;mm\n*** Rod/Stroke : 1.48\n*** Compression : 9.9:1<ref name=\"Honda Civic Coupe Owner's Manual\"/>\n*** Power : {{convert|125|PS|kW hp|0|abbr=on}} at 6,300&nbsp;rpm<ref name=\"Honda Certificate of Conformity\"/>\n*** Torque : {{convert|145|Nm|lbft|0|abbr=on}} at 4,800&nbsp;rpm<ref name=\"Honda Certificate of Conformity\"/>\n*** RPM redline: 6,800&nbsp;rpm\n*** Rev-limiter: 7,200&nbsp;rpm\n*** Valvetrain: SOHC VTEC-E, four valves per cylinder\n*** VTEC Switchover: 2,500 - 3,200&nbsp;rpm\n*** Fuel Control: OBD-2 MPFI\n\n===D17Z3===\n* [[VTEC#SOHC VTEC|VTEC]]\n* Found in:\n** 2001\u20132006 Honda Civic EX (Brazil only)\n** 2005\u20132006 Honda Civic LXL (Brazil only)\n*** Displacement: {{convert|1668|cc|CID|abbr=on}}\n*** Bore and Stroke: {{convert|75|x|94.4|mm|in|abbr=on}}\n*** Rod Length: 140&nbsp;mm\n*** Rod/Stroke: 1.48\n*** Compression: 9.9:1\n*** Power: {{convert|130|hp|kW PS|0|abbr=on}} at 6,300&nbsp;rpm<br><ref name=\"AR02.300\">''[[#AR02|Automobil Revue 2002]]'', p. 300</ref>\n*** Torque: 114&nbsp;lb\u00b7ft (15.8&nbsp;kg/m, 154 Nm) at 4,800&nbsp;rpm<ref name=\"Specs sedan\">{{cite web | title = 2001 Honda Civic Sedan Specifications (News Release) | url = http://www.honda.com/newsandviews/article.aspx?id=20010104001153 | publisher = American Honda Motor Company | date = 2000-09-15 | accessdate = 2012-01-30}}</ref><br>Japan: {{convert|154|Nm|lbft|0|abbr=on}} at 4,800&nbsp;rpm<ref name=\"AR02.300\"/>\n*** RPM redline: 6,800&nbsp;rpm\n*** Rev-limiter: 7,000&nbsp;rpm\n*** Valvetrain: SOHC VTEC, four valves per cylinder\n*** VTEC Switchover: 4,800&nbsp;rpm\n*** Fuel Control: OBD-2 MPFI\n\n===D17Z2===\n* [[SOHC]]\n* Found in:\n** 2001\u20132006 Honda Civic LX (Brazil only)\n** 2004 Honda Civic LXL (Brazil only)\n*** Displacement: {{convert|1668|cc|CID|abbr=on}}\n*** Bore and Stroke: {{convert|75|x|94.4|mm|in|abbr=on}}\n*** Rod Length: 140&nbsp;mm\n*** Rod/Stroke: 1.48\n*** Compression: 9.9:1\n*** Power: {{convert|115|hp|kW PS|0|abbr=on}} at 6,300&nbsp;rpm<br><ref name=\"AR02.300\">''[[#AR02|Automobil Revue 2002]]'', p. 300</ref>\n*** Torque: 114&nbsp;lb\u00b7ft (15.8&nbsp;kg/m, 154 Nm) at 4,800&nbsp;rpm<ref name=\"Specs sedan\">{{cite web | title = 2001 Honda Civic Sedan Specifications (News Release) | url = http://www.honda.com/newsandviews/article.aspx?id=20010104001153 | publisher = American Honda Motor Company | date = 2000-09-15 | accessdate = 2012-01-30}}</ref><br>Japan: {{convert|154|Nm|lbft|0|abbr=on}} at 4,800&nbsp;rpm<ref name=\"AR02.300\"/>\n*** RPM redline: 6,800&nbsp;rpm\n*** Rev-limiter: 7,000&nbsp;rpm\n*** Valvetrain: SOHC, four valves per cylinder\n*** Fuel Control: OBD-2 MPFI\n\n== References ==\n* {{cite book | ref = AR97 | title = Automobil Revue 1997 | editor-last = B\u00fcschi | editor-first = Hans-Ulrich | publisher = Hallwag AG | location = Berne, Switzerland | language = German, French | volume = 92 |date=6 March 1997 | isbn = 3-444-10479-0 }}\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n\n{{Honda}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Honda D Engine}}\n[[Category:Honda engines|D]]\n[[Category:Inline-four engines]]\n", "text_old": "[[File:D16common.jpg|thumb|D16Y8 Engine]]\n[[File:Honda D15B6.JPG|thumb|D15B6 Engine]]\n[[File:HondaD15b3stage.jpg|thumb|D15B [[3-stage VTEC]] Engine]]\n\nThe Honda D series [[Inline-four engine|inline-four cylinder]] engine is used in a variety of compact models, most commonly the [[Honda Civic]], [[Honda CRX|CRX]], [[Honda Logo|Logo]], [[Honda Stream|Stream]], and first-generation [[Honda Integra|Integra]]. Engine displacement ranges between 1.2 and 1.7 liters. The D Series engine is either [[SOHC]] or [[DOHC]], and might include [[VTEC]] variable valve timing. Power ranges from {{convert|66|PS|kW|0|abbr=on}} in the [[Honda Logo|Logo]] to {{Convert|130|PS|kW|0|abbr=on}} in the Civic Si. D-series production commenced 1984 and ended 2005. D-series engine technology culminated with production of the D15B [[3-stage VTEC]] (D15Z7) which was available in markets outside of the United States. Earlier versions of this engine also used a single port fuel injection system Honda called PGM-CARB, signifying the carburetor was computer controlled.\n\n==D12 series engines (1.2 liter) {{anchor|D12}}==\n\n===D12B1===\n\n* Found in:\n** 1988-1990 Honda Civic (European Market)\n*** Displacement: {{convert|1193|cc|CID|1|abbr=on|lk=out}}\n*** Bore and Stroke: {{convert|75.0|x|67.5|mm|in|abbr=on}}\n*** Compression: 8,6:1\n*** Power: {{convert|74|PS|kW hp|0|abbr=on}} at 6300&nbsp;rpm\n*** Torque: {{convert|88|Nm|kgm|1|abbr=on}} at 3500&nbsp;rpm\n*** Valvetrain: SOHC (4 valves per cylinder)\n*** Fuel Control: Single Carburetor PGM-CARB\n\n==D13 series engines (1.3 liter) {{anchor|D13}}==\n\n===D13B1===\n\n* Found in:\n** 1988\u20131995 Honda Civic EC (European Market)\n*** Displacement : {{convert|1343|cc|CID|1|abbr=on|lk=out}}\n*** Bore and Stroke : {{convert|75.0|x|76.0|mm|in|abbr=on}}\n*** Compression : 9.5:1\n*** Power : {{convert|76|PS|kW hp|0|abbr=on}} at 6300&nbsp;rpm\n*** Torque: {{convert|102|Nm|kgm|1|abbr=on}} at 3100&nbsp;rpm\n*** Valvetrain : SOHC (4 valves per cylinder)\n*** Fuel Control : Single Carburetor PGM-CARB\n\n===D13B2===\n\n* Found in:\n** 1992\u20131995 Honda Civic DX/EX (European Market)\n*** Displacement: {{convert|1343|cc|CID|1|abbr=on}}\n*** Bore and Stroke: {{convert|75.0|x|76.0|mm|in|abbr=on}}\n*** Compression: 9:1\n*** Power: {{convert|75|PS|kW hp|0|abbr=on}} at 6300&nbsp;rpm<ref name=\"AR94\">{{cite book | title = Automobil Revue 1994 | editor-last = B\u00fcschi | editor-first = Hans-Ulrich | publisher = Hallwag AG | location = Berne, Switzerland | language = German, French | page = 296 | volume = 89 |date=10 March 1994 | isbn = 3-444-00584-9 }}</ref>\n*** Torque: {{convert|102|Nm|kgm lbft|abbr=on}} at 3100&nbsp;rpm<ref name=\"AR94\"/>\n*** Valvetrain: SOHC, four valves per cylinder\n*** Cam Gear: 38 teeth\n*** Piston Code: PM1G\n*** Head Code: PM3\n*** Fuel Control: Single electronic carburettor PGM-CARB\n*** ECU: P01  OBD-0\n\n===D13B4===\n\n* Found in:\n** 1996\u20132002 Honda City LXi/EXi/DX, 1995-2000 [[Honda Civic (sixth generation)|Honda Civic EK2]]\n*** Displacement : {{convert|1343|cc|CID|1|abbr=on}}\n*** Bore and Stroke : {{convert|75.0|x|76.0|mm|in|abbr=on}}\n*** Compression:    9.75:1\n*** Power: {{convert|95|PS|kW|abbr=on}} at 6500&nbsp;rpm<ref name=AR97.1>''[[#AR97|Automobil Revue 1997]], p. 291</ref> (City)<br>{{pad|3em}}{{convert|91|PS|kW|abbr=on}} at 6,300&nbsp;rpm<ref name=AR97.2>''[[#AR97|Automobil Revue 1997]], p. 292</ref> (Civic)\n*** Torque: {{convert|119|Nm|kgm lbft|abbr=on}} at 4700&nbsp;rpm<ref name=AR97.1/> (City)<br>{{pad|3em}}{{convert|114|Nm|kgm lbft|abbr=on}} at 4800&nbsp;rpm<ref name=AR97.2/> (Civic)\n*** Valvetrain : SOHC (four valves per cylinder), 16 valves\n*** Fuel Control : Multi-point fuel Injection, PGM-FI\n\n===D13B7===\n\n* Found in:\n** 1998\u20132001 Honda Logo 3D/5D\n*** Displacement : {{convert|1343|cc|CID|1|abbr=on}}\n*** Bore and Stroke : 75.0 x 76.0&nbsp;mm\n*** Compression : 9.2\n*** Power : {{convert|66|PS|kW hp|1|abbr=on}} at 5000&nbsp;rpm\n*** Torque : {{convert|11.3|kgm|1|abbr=on}} at 2500&nbsp;rpm\n*** Valvetrain : SOHC (2 valves per cylinder)\n*** Fuel Control : Multi-point fuel Injection, PGM-FI\n\n===D13C===\n\n* Found in:\n** 1989\u20131994 Honda City CE, CE Fit, CE Select, CG, CR-i, CR-i limited, CZ-i, New Fit (Japanese Market)\n*** Displacement : {{convert|1296|cc|CID|1|abbr=on}}\n*** Bore and Stroke : 73.7mm x 76.0&nbsp;mm\n*** Compression : 9.6:1\n*** Power : {{convert|100|PS|kW hp|1|abbr=on}} at 6500&nbsp;rpm\n*** Torque : {{convert|11.6|kgm|Nm lbft|1|abbr=on}} at 5500&nbsp;rpm\n*** Valvetrain : SOHC (4 valves per cylinder)\n*** Fuel Control : Multi-point fuel Injection, PGM-FI\n\n==D14 series engines (1.4 liter) {{anchor|D14}}==\n\n===D14A1===\n* Found in:\n** 1987\u20131991 Honda Civic GL and 1990 CRX (European market)\n** October 1989 \u2013 1994 Honda Concerto GL (European market)\n*** Displacement: {{convert|1396|cc|CID|abbr=on}}\n*** Bore and Stroke: {{convert|75.0|x|79.0|mm|in|abbr=on}}\n*** Compression: 9.3:1\n*** Power: {{convert|90|PS|kW hp|0|abbr=on}} at 6,300&nbsp;rpm<ref name=TAM901>{{Cite book | title = Quattroruote: Tutte le Auto del Mondo 1990 | editor = Mastrostefano, Raffaele | publisher = Editoriale Domus S.p.A | year = 1990 | pages = 344, 351 | language = Italian | location = Milano }}</ref><br>{{pad|3.3em}}{{convert|88|PS|kW hp|0|abbr=on}} in the Concerto<ref name=TAM902>''Tutte le Auto del Mondo 1990'', p. 353</ref>\n*** Torque: {{convert|11.4|kgm|Nm lbft|abbr=on}} at 4,500&nbsp;rpm\n*** Valvetrain: SOHC (four valves per cylinder)\n*** Fuel Control: Dual Carburetor PGM-CARB\n*** Piston Code: PM2\n\n===D14A2===\n* Found in:\n** 1995\u20131997 Honda Civic MA8 (European Market)\n*** Displacement : {{convert|1396|cc|CID|abbr=on}}\n*** Bore and Stroke : {{convert|75.0|x|79.0|mm|in|abbr=on}}\n*** Compression : 9.2:1\n*** ECU code: P1J\n*** Power : 89&nbsp;hp (66.4&nbsp;kW, 90.2 ps) at 6,100&nbsp;rpm\n*** Torque : 86&nbsp;lb\u00b7ft (11.9&nbsp;kg/m, 117 Nm) at 5,000&nbsp;rpm\n*** Valvetrain : SOHC (4 valves per cylinder)\n*** Fuel Control : OBD-1, MPFIMulti-point fuel Injection, PGM-FI\n*** Redline : 6,800&nbsp;rpm\n*** Fuel cutout : 7,250&nbsp;rpm\n\n===D14A3===\n* Found in:\n** 1996\u20132000 Honda Civic 1.4i EJ9 (European Market)\n*** Displacement : {{convert|1396|cc|CID|abbr=on}}\n*** Bore and Stroke : {{convert|75.0|x|79.0|mm|in|abbr=on}}\n*** Compression : 9.1:1\n*** ECU code: P3X\n*** Power : {{convert|75|PS|kW hp|0|abbr=on}} at 6,000&nbsp;rpm<ref name=\"BK00\"/>\n*** Torque : {{convert|109|Nm|kgm lbft|abbr=on}} at 3,000&nbsp;rpm<ref name=\"BK00\"/>\n*** Valvetrain : SOHC (4 valves per cylinder), non VTEC\n*** Redline : 6,800&nbsp;rpm\n*** Fuel cut: 7,200&nbsp;rpm\n*** Fuel Control : OBD2-a, DPFI (SFi \u2013 Simplified Fuel injection), 1+3 2+4 injectors thrown together\n*** Transmission: S40\n\n===D14A4===\n* Found in:\n** 1996\u20131998 Honda Civic 1.4iS EJ9 (European Market)\n*** Displacement : {{convert|1396|cc|CID|1|abbr=on}}\n*** Bore and Stroke : {{convert|75.0|x|79.0|mm|in|abbr=on}}\n*** Compression : 9.1:1\n*** Piston code: P3Y\n*** Piston Compression height: 29.5&nbsp;mm\n*** Piston dish volume: -5.4&nbsp;cc\n*** ECU code: P3Y\n*** Big-end bore: 43&nbsp;mm\n*** Rod length(center to center): 138&nbsp;mm\n*** Power : {{convert|90|PS|kW hp|0|abbr=on}} at 6,300&nbsp;rpm<ref name=\"BK00\">{{cite book | title = Bilkatalogen 2000 ''(Swedish edition of German'' Auto Katalog'')'' | language = Swedish | editor = \u00c5hman, Michael | publisher = Auto Motor & Sport Sverige AB | location = Solna, Sweden | pages = 202\u2013203 | year = 1999 }}</ref>\n*** Torque : {{convert|124|Nm|kgm lbft|abbr=on}} at 4,500&nbsp;rpm<ref name=\"BK00\"/>\n*** Valvetrain : SOHC, four valves per cylinder, non VTEC\n*** Red line : 6,800&nbsp;rpm\n*** Fuel cut: 7,200&nbsp;rpm\n*** Fuel Control : OBD2-a, DPFI (SFi \u2013 Simplified Fuel injection), 1+3 2+4 injectors thrown together\n*** Transmission : S40 (or S4PA for 4AT)\n*** Deck Height : 207&nbsp;mm\n\nThe D14A3 and D14A4 engines are identical, the difference is only one small gasket under the throttle body in D14A3 which restricts the air intake of the engine, this happen in some European countries.\n\n===D14A5===\n* Found in:\n** 1995 - 1997 Honda Civic MA8 (European Market)\n*** Displacement : {{convert|1396|cc|CID|abbr=on}}\n*** Bore and Stroke : {{co