they came to a charity function with a huge amount of money and they have to give the money to orphan children.\n\n===''Double Dhamaal'' (2011)===\n{{Main|Double Dhamaal}}\nThe story continues from the previous film. The four good-for-nothing friends Roy ([[Ritesh Deshmukh|Ritesh]]), Adi ([[Arshad Warsi|Arshad]]), Manav ([[Jaaved Jaaferi|Jaaved]]) and Boman ([[Aashish Chaudhary|Aashish]]), are still conning people for a living. One day, they see their enemy Kabir ([[Sanjay Dutt]]) driving a luxurious [[Mercedes Benz]], and disguise themselves to find out the secret behind his success. They investigate and find that he lives off his wife's wealth. They then blackmail him into making them his business partners, but little do the four idiots know that Kabir and his wife Kamini ([[Mallika Sherawat|Mallika]]) along with his sister Kiya ([[Kangana Ranaut|Ranaut]]) have an agenda of their own. Kabir connects them with an investor named Bata Bhai ([[Satish Kaushik]]) who is also a part-time don. The four friends steal Bata Bhai's money, and the money is then stolen by Kabir and his family. Kabir leaves the country along with his family and leaves the four idiots to get killed by Bata Bhai. However, the four friends leave the city and manage to track Kabir down in [[Macau]]. They make a plan to ruin Kabir's happiness and take their money back by going in disguise. Roy cons Kiya by pretending to be in love with her, whilst Adi pretends to be Kabir's secretary.\n\n===''Total Dhamaal'' (2019)===\n{{Main|Total Dhamaal}}\nThe film does not continue the story from the previous films and is a fresh story.\n\nGuddu ([[Ajay Devgn]]) and Jonny ([[Sanjay Mishra (actor)|Sanjay Mishra]]), small-time conmen get double-crossed of their illegal booty by their own colleague Pintu ([[Manoj Pahwa]]) after which starts a mad crazy adventure between Guddu-Jonny and 4 other groups i.e Avinash ([[Anil Kapoor]]) and Bindu ([[Madhuri Dixit]]) - a bickering couple about to be divorced; Lallan ([[Riteish Deshmukh]]) and Jhingur ([[Pitobash Tripathy]]) - Fire officers turned offenders; a police commissioner ([[Boman Irani]]) and his sidekick Inspector ([[Vijay Patkar]]); and two weird siblings Aditya ([[Arshad Warsi]]) and Manav ([[Javed Jaffrey]]) for {{INRConvert|50|c}} which was hidden by Pintu in Omkar Zoo in Janakpur.\n\n===''Full On Dhamaal'' (TBA)===\nAfter the trailer release of '''[[Total Dhamaal]]''', in an interview, director [[Indra Kumar]] said that another '''Dhamaal''' sequel is definitely on the cards and added that he has already registered two titles - '''Triple Dhamaal''' and '''Full On Dhamaal''' - for the next {{not a typo|installment}} of the franchise. \nWith the third film named '''[[Total Dhamaal]]''', the fourth film will most probably be titled '''Full On Dhamaal'''.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://m.timesofindia.com/entertainment/hindi/bollywood/photo-features/movies-to-look-forward-to/total-dhamaal-director-indra-kumar-plans-next-instalment-registers-two-titles-triple-dhamaal-and-full-on-dhamaal/photostory/67635066.cms|website=Times of India|title= 'Total Dhamaal' director Indra Kumar plans next instalment; registers two titles - 'Triple Dhamaal' and 'Full On Dhamaal'|date=22 January 2019|access-date=11 March 2019}}</ref> \n\n[[Sanjay Dutt]] and [[Aashish Chaudhary]] who were part of first two films but not the third film are expected to return for the fourth film along with [[Ajay Devgn]], [[Riteish Deshmukh]], [[Arshad Warsi]], [[Javed Jaffrey]].\n\n==Cast and characters==\n<blockquote class=\"toccolours\" style=\"text-align:justify; width:95%; float:center; padding: 5px 5px 5px 5px; display:table;\">\n<center>'''List indicator(s)'''</center>\n* This table shows characters that have appeared in one or more films in the series.\n* An empty dark grey cell indicates that the character was not in the film, or that the character's presence in the film has yet to be announced.\n* {{note label|young|Y|}} indicates a role as a younger version of the character.\n* {{note label|old|O|}} indicates a role as an older version of the character.\n* {{note label|uncredited|U|}} indicates an uncredited role.\n* {{note label|cameo|C|}} indicates a cameo role.\n* {{note label|voice|V|}} indicates a voice-only role\n* {{note label|stills|S|}} indicates a stills or photographs role.\n* {{note label|archive|A|}} indicates an appearance through archival footage.\n</blockquote>\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"text-align:center;\" width=\"100%\"\n|-\n! rowspan=\"2\" | Character\n! colspan=\"4\" | Film\n|-\n!  width:33%;\"| ''[[Dhamaal]]'' <br>(2007)\n!  width:33%;\"| ''[[Double Dhamaal]]'' <br>(2011)\n!  width:33%;\"| ''[[Total Dhamaal]]'' <br>(2019)\n!  width:33%;\"| ''[[Full on Dhamaal]]'' <br>(TBA)\n|-\n! Deshbandhu Roy / Lallan\n| colspan=\"4\" | [[Riteish Deshmukh]]\n|-\n! Aditya \"Adi\" Shrivastav\n| colspan=\"4\" | [[Arshad Warsi]]\n|-\n! Manav Shrivastav\n| colspan=\"4\" | [[Jaaved Jaffrey]]\n|-\n! Kabir Nayak\n| colspan=\"2\" | [[Sanjay Dutt]]\n|colspan=\"1\" style=\"background:#d3d3d3;\"|\n|[[Sanjay Dutt]]\n|-\n! Boman Contractor\n| colspan=\"2\" | [[Ashish Chaudhary]]\n|colspan=\"1\" style=\"background:#d3d3d3;\"|\n|[[Ashish Chaudhary]]\n|-\n! Babubhai / Jonny\n| [[Sanjay Mishra (actor)|Sanjay Mishra]]\n| colspan=\"1\" style=\"background:#d3d3d3;\"|\n| colspan=\"2\" |[[Sanjay Mishra (actor)|Sanjay Mishra]]\n|-\n! Kamini\n| style=\"background:#d3d3d3;\"|\n| [[Mallika Sherawat]]\n| colspan=\"2\" style=\"background:#d3d3d3;\"|\n|-\n! Kiya Nayak\n| style=\"background:#d3d3d3;\"|\n| [[Kangana Ranaut]]\n| colspan=\"2\" style=\"background:#d3d3d3;\"|\n|-\n! Baba Batanand Swami\n| style=\"background:#d3d3d3;\"|\n| [[Satish Kaushik]]\n| colspan=\"2\" style=\"background:#d3d3d3;\"|\n|-\n! Avinash Patel\n| colspan=\"2\" style=\"background:#d3d3d3;\"|\n| [[Anil Kapoor]] \n| style=\"background:#d3d3d3;\"|\n|-\n! Guddu\n| colspan=\"2\" style=\"background:#d3d3d3;\"|\n| colspan=\"2\" | [[Ajay Devgn]]\n|-\n! Bindu\n| colspan=\"2\" style=\"background:#d3d3d3;\"|\n| [[Madhuri Dixit]] \n| style=\"background:#d3d3d3;\"|\n|-\n|}\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* {{IMDb title|0845448}}\n* {{Bollywoodhungama|12648}}\n* {{Official website|http://www.doubledhamaalmovie.com/}}\n* {{IMDb title|1728239}}\n* {{Bollywoodhungama|14060}}\n*[http://www.bollywoodhungama.com/movie/total-dhamaal/ ''Total Dhamaal''] at [[Bollywood Hungama]]\n\n{{Dhamaal series}}\n\n[[Category:Hindi-language films]]\n[[Category:Indian film series]]\n[[Category:Comedy film series]]\n", "name_user": "CAPTAIN RAJU", "label": "safe", "comment": "clean up,typo(s) fixed: i.e  \u2192 i.e.", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Dhamaal_(film_series)"}
